lita also hopes that she'll have someone else explain how the baby is going to be born, remembering some of the stories about Celaneo, it made her cringe just a touch. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theseusofthemiscrya>Theseus of Themiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#993300>(6/10/03 6:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/ixltheseuslxl/myhomepage/theseus1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coming Home</span><hr size=1> Theseus rolled over to face the fire, his eyes sliding open as he stared at the dancing flames still somewhat asleep.  His stomach growled, then his eyes settled on the thick blanket and the pillow waiting for him.  He listened quietly as the girls spoke back and forth.  He looked over at Celaneo, his eyes widening slightly as she looked more pregnant than she had before he'd gone to sleep.  His eyes were still heavy with sleep and he could have probably slept longer, but he slowly sat up, stretching lightly against the side of the hut.  &quot;I hope the rains do not come early this year.&quot;  His statement was rather out of the blue and he hadn't truly realized he'd spoken.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=celaneo@amazonsunite>Celaneo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#993300>(6/10/03 6:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&in