me</span><hr size=1> Theseus sort of frowned at the demand to go back to sleep.    He glanced over at Celaneo and settled back down this time with the pillow tucked under his head.  He didn't bother with the blanket just yet.  His eyes moved over Kalasin and Lalita as they spoke together.   He was not sure if this was the place for him.  Perhaps he truly did not belong here and it was only his longing to belong that had poisoned his common sense.  He was only treated well because of who his mother was and that was the wrong reason to stay. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=battlingangel>Battling Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#993300>(6/10/03 9:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.speedis.org/images/214.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coming Home</span><hr size=1> Kalasin shrugged. She had not kept much track of time since she had arrived. “I wouldn’t know. It could be anything between two weeks and two months.” She replied quite quickly. “Things have been slow, very slow.”<br>
She sighed as she felt the pain rising up inside her again, she would need to rest soon. If she did not, she would collapse on the spot, not a good way to be presented to anyone. In her head, she cursed the man that had done this to her, even though she knew that no amount of curses would do. There were not enough.<br>
Slowly, she stood.<br>
“I am sorry, but I must have a brief rest, perhaps half of an hour?”<br>
As she took a few steps backwards, it was plain to see that she was limping, something that she had not been doing before. Kalasin cursed out loud in Vezrit for showing any sign of weakness. She was comfortable to use Vezrit, the language of her deceased mother extinct nomadic people. She knew that aside from her sister Dreyanne, no other person knew of it, and so she knew that if she wished to curse herself for any reason, this would be the best language in which to do so. She switched back to her fragmented Greek to address the people before her.<br>
“I will come back after that and finish this conversation, but for now I must rest, if not, I do fear the consequences.”<br>
